"{\"uid\": \"english.aawsat.com-opinion-5051202-paris-olympics-day-after\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Many had dismissed it as a costly indulgence for a nation facing economic hardship while some condemned it as a dangerous diversion from the deepest political crisis France faces since the 1950s.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 195, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 166, \"end\": 172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.7456634192783995, \"rank\": 0.3371460324558364, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a costly indulgence\", \"from\": 25, \"to\": 44}, {\"ngram\": \"a nation\", \"from\": 49, \"to\": 57}, {\"ngram\": \"economic hardship\", \"from\": 65, \"to\": 82}, {\"ngram\": \"a dangerous diversion\", \"from\": 110, \"to\": 131}, {\"ngram\": \"the deepest political crisis\", \"from\": 137, \"to\": 165}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And, yet, the two-week' long summer Olympics hosted by Paris is now universally lauded as a success in organizational, artistic, and of course sporting terms.\", \"from\": 197, \"to\": 355, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 252, \"end\": 257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.021800727630018e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the two-week' long summer Olympics\", \"from\": 207, \"to\": 241}, {\"ngram\": \"a success\", \"from\": 287, \"to\": 296}, {\"ngram\": \"course\", \"from\": 333, \"to\": 339}, {\"ngram\": \"terms\", \"from\": 349, \"to\": 354}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For two whole weeks the usually grumpy French, some of them in civil war mood sheathed their daggers to have a good time together.\", \"from\": 356, \"to\": 486, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"two whole weeks\", \"from\": 360, \"to\": 375}, {\"ngram\": \"civil war mood\", \"from\": 419, \"to\": 433}, {\"ngram\": \"their daggers\", \"from\": 443, \"to\": 456}, {\"ngram\": \"a good time\", \"from\": 465, \"to\": 476}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The old ditty that sport unites while politics divides sounded more plausible than ever.\", \"from\": 488, \"to\": 576, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The old ditty\", \"from\": 488, \"to\": 501}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 507, \"to\": 512}, {\"ngram\": \"politics\", \"from\": 526, \"to\": 534}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The fact that man does not live by bread alone has been known ever since humanity acquired the minimum of security without which no metaphysical speculation is possible.\", \"from\": 578, \"to\": 747, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The fact\", \"from\": 578, \"to\": 586}, {\"ngram\": \"man\", \"from\": 592, \"to\": 595}, {\"ngram\": \"bread\", \"from\": 613, \"to\": 618}, {\"ngram\": \"humanity\", \"from\": 651, \"to\": 659}, {\"ngram\": \"the minimum\", \"from\": 669, \"to\": 680}, {\"ngram\": \"security\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 692}, {\"ngram\": \"no metaphysical speculation\", \"from\": 707, \"to\": 734}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Almost 2,000 years ago, the Roman Emperor Nero understood that running an empire requires both bread and circus.\", \"from\": 749, \"to\": 861, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 777, \"end\": 782, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"score\": 0.8317051256441325, \"rank\": 0.20159929852772623, \"text\": \"Roman\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an empire\", \"from\": 820, \"to\": 829}, {\"ngram\": \"both bread\", \"from\": 839, \"to\": 849}, {\"ngram\": \"circus\", \"from\": 854, \"to\": 860}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Once the citizens have filled their bellies, they seek amusement which the emperor provides by having gladiators fighting each other to death or parading exotic animals from the four corners of the earth.\", \"from\": 862, \"to\": 1066, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the citizens\", \"from\": 867, \"to\": 879}, {\"ngram\": \"their bellies\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 905}, {\"ngram\": \"amusement\", \"from\": 917, \"to\": 926}, {\"ngram\": \"the emperor\", \"from\": 933, \"to\": 944}, {\"ngram\": \"gladiators\", \"from\": 964, \"to\": 974}, {\"ngram\": \"death\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1003}, {\"ngram\": \"exotic animals\", \"from\": 1016, \"to\": 1030}, {\"ngram\": \"the four corners\", \"from\": 1036, \"to\": 1052}, {\"ngram\": \"the earth\", \"from\": 1056, \"to\": 1065}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a different register, the German philosopher, Schopenhauer, diagnosed the main affliction of the post-Industrial Revolution man as boredom.\", \"from\": 1068, \"to\": 1210, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1097, \"end\": 1103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.8043383113144604, \"rank\": 0.1855951172525552, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 1117, \"end\": 1129, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arthur_Schopenhauer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Schopenhauer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arthur_Schopenhauer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arthur_Schopenhauer\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a different register\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1091}, {\"ngram\": \"the main affliction\", \"from\": 1141, \"to\": 1160}, {\"ngram\": \"the post-Industrial Revolution man\", \"from\": 1164, \"to\": 1198}, {\"ngram\": \"boredom\", \"from\": 1202, \"to\": 1209}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to him, even before the Industrial revolution, it was the need to escape from boredom that put Alexander on the route to world conquest.\", \"from\": 1211, \"to\": 1357, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1316, \"end\": 1325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_the_Great\", \"score\": 0.9999998394246306, \"rank\": 1.4226886128041445e-07, \"text\": \"Alexander\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_the_Great\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_the_Great\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Industrial revolution\", \"from\": 1241, \"to\": 1266}, {\"ngram\": \"the need\", \"from\": 1275, \"to\": 1283}, {\"ngram\": \"boredom\", \"from\": 1299, \"to\": 1306}, {\"ngram\": \"the route\", \"from\": 1329, \"to\": 1338}, {\"ngram\": \"world conquest\", \"from\": 1342, \"to\": 1356}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Avoiding boredom also forced men to become travelers, explorers and eventually, itinerant traders, and colonizers.\", \"from\": 1359, \"to\": 1473, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"boredom\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1375}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 1388, \"to\": 1391}, {\"ngram\": \"travelers\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1411}, {\"ngram\": \"explorers\", \"from\": 1413, \"to\": 1422}, {\"ngram\": \"eventually, itinerant traders\", \"from\": 1427, \"to\": 1456}, {\"ngram\": \"colonizers\", \"from\": 1462, \"to\": 1472}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The need to shed boredom could also lead to civil or foreign wars.\", \"from\": 1474, \"to\": 1540, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The need\", \"from\": 1474, \"to\": 1482}, {\"ngram\": \"boredom\", \"from\": 1491, \"to\": 1498}, {\"ngram\": \"civil or foreign wars\", \"from\": 1518, \"to\": 1539}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In lighter mode tourism, the world's biggest trade in terms of dollars earned, is also a mechanism for escaping boredom.\", \"from\": 1541, \"to\": 1661, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"lighter mode tourism\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1564}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's biggest trade\", \"from\": 1566, \"to\": 1591}, {\"ngram\": \"terms\", \"from\": 1595, \"to\": 1600}, {\"ngram\": \"dollars\", \"from\": 1604, \"to\": 1611}, {\"ngram\": \"a mechanism\", \"from\": 1628, \"to\": 1639}, {\"ngram\": \"boredom\", \"from\": 1653, \"to\": 1660}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In modern democracies, general elections could offer some relief from boredom.\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1741, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"modern democracies\", \"from\": 1666, \"to\": 1684}, {\"ngram\": \"general elections\", \"from\": 1686, \"to\": 1703}, {\"ngram\": \"some relief\", \"from\": 1716, \"to\": 1727}, {\"ngram\": \"boredom\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 1740}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But what if they turn out generating another form of boredom as the latest French general election did?\", \"from\": 1742, \"to\": 1845, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1817, \"end\": 1823, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.879617539671701, \"rank\": 0.09470987637235428, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"another form\", \"from\": 1779, \"to\": 1791}, {\"ngram\": \"boredom\", \"from\": 1795, \"to\": 1802}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Post-elections, the French were left with a blurred picture; it was like watching paint dry.\", \"from\": 1847, \"to\": 1939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1867, \"end\": 1873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.879617539671701, \"rank\": 0.09470987637235428, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"elections\", \"from\": 1852, \"to\": 1861}, {\"ngram\": \"a blurred picture\", \"from\": 1889, \"to\": 1906}, {\"ngram\": \"paint\", \"from\": 1929, \"to\": 1934}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The country seemed to have chosen a new parliament in a way that it could not function as a parliament.\", \"from\": 1941, \"to\": 2044, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The country\", \"from\": 1941, \"to\": 1952}, {\"ngram\": \"a new parliament\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 1991}, {\"ngram\": \"a way\", \"from\": 1995, \"to\": 2000}, {\"ngram\": \"a parliament\", \"from\": 2031, \"to\": 2043}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Worse still, unlike the British general election that produced a new government within hours of results being announced, the French version opened the prospect of either having no new government or having too many succeeding each other after a few days or weeks.\", \"from\": 2045, \"to\": 2307, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2069, \"end\": 2076, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9160780169580219, \"rank\": 0.0916073508741198, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 2170, \"end\": 2176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.879617539671701, \"rank\": 0.09470987637235428, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a new government\", \"from\": 2108, \"to\": 2124}, {\"ngram\": \"hours\", \"from\": 2132, \"to\": 2137}, {\"ngram\": \"results\", \"from\": 2141, \"to\": 2148}, {\"ngram\": \"the prospect\", \"from\": 2192, \"to\": 2204}, {\"ngram\": \"no new government\", \"from\": 2222, \"to\": 2239}, {\"ngram\": \"a few days\", \"from\": 2287, \"to\": 2297}, {\"ngram\": \"weeks\", \"from\": 2301, \"to\": 2306}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics put all those concerns on hold-for two weeks, a parenthesis that might remain half open until the end of the para-Olympics in mid-September.\", \"from\": 2309, \"to\": 2462, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympics\", \"from\": 2309, \"to\": 2321}, {\"ngram\": \"all those concerns\", \"from\": 2326, \"to\": 2344}, {\"ngram\": \"hold\", \"from\": 2348, \"to\": 2352}, {\"ngram\": \"two weeks\", \"from\": 2357, \"to\": 2366}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 2416, \"to\": 2423}, {\"ngram\": \"the para-Olympics\", \"from\": 2427, \"to\": 2444}, {\"ngram\": \"mid\", \"from\": 2448, \"to\": 2451}, {\"ngram\": \"September\", \"from\": 2452, \"to\": 2461}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But, what then?\", \"from\": 2464, \"to\": 2479, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The French Constitution, tailored for General de Gaulle in 1958, is a monarchic concoction disguised as a republican scheme.\", \"from\": 2481, \"to\": 2605, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2519, \"end\": 2536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_de_Gaulle\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"General de Gaulle\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_de_Gaulle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_de_Gaulle\"}, {\"begin\": 2587, \"end\": 2597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republicanism\", \"score\": 0.9354323448943186, \"rank\": 0.0690243980287374, \"text\": \"republican\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republicanism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republicanism\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The French Constitution\", \"from\": 2481, \"to\": 2504}, {\"ngram\": \"a monarchic concoction\", \"from\": 2549, \"to\": 2571}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In it, the President names the Prime Minister and his Cabinet, but they are not able to act as such without the consent of a parliamentary majority.\", \"from\": 2606, \"to\": 2754, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2660, \"end\": 2667, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cabinet_of_the_United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9142586644033277, \"rank\": 0.05006109951586184, \"text\": \"Cabinet\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cabinet_of_the_United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cabinet_of_the_United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the President\", \"from\": 2613, \"to\": 2626}, {\"ngram\": \"the Prime Minister\", \"from\": 2633, \"to\": 2651}, {\"ngram\": \"the consent\", \"from\": 2714, \"to\": 2725}, {\"ngram\": \"a parliamentary majority\", \"from\": 2729, \"to\": 2753}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since the new parliament is divided into four blocs, with half-blocs within each of them finding even a simple majority is a Herculean task.\", \"from\": 2756, \"to\": 2896, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the new parliament\", \"from\": 2762, \"to\": 2780}, {\"ngram\": \"four blocs\", \"from\": 2797, \"to\": 2807}, {\"ngram\": \"half-blocs\", \"from\": 2814, \"to\": 2824}, {\"ngram\": \"even a simple majority\", \"from\": 2853, \"to\": 2875}, {\"ngram\": \"a Herculean task\", \"from\": 2879, \"to\": 2895}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Needless to say French political parties have no experience of coalition building beyond coming together around a charismatic leader the kind of horse-trading prevalent in the rest of the European Union is unthinkable in France.\", \"from\": 2897, \"to\": 3125, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3094, \"end\": 3099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999995984581, \"rank\": 3.9367766139289827e-10, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3118, \"end\": 3124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.7456634192783995, \"rank\": 0.3371460324558364, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"French political parties\", \"from\": 2913, \"to\": 2937}, {\"ngram\": \"no experience\", \"from\": 2943, \"to\": 2956}, {\"ngram\": \"coalition building\", \"from\": 2960, \"to\": 2978}, {\"ngram\": \"a charismatic leader\", \"from\": 3009, \"to\": 3029}, {\"ngram\": \"the kind\", \"from\": 3030, \"to\": 3038}, {\"ngram\": \"horse-trading prevalent\", \"from\": 3042, \"to\": 3065}, {\"ngram\": \"the rest\", \"from\": 3069, \"to\": 3077}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As no constitutional limit is set for the president's decision to name a new government, the nation could be left on autopilot with a caretaker government dealing with routine matters for unspecified lapse of time.\", \"from\": 3127, \"to\": 3341, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no constitutional limit\", \"from\": 3130, \"to\": 3153}, {\"ngram\": \"the president's decision\", \"from\": 3165, \"to\": 3189}, {\"ngram\": \"a new government\", \"from\": 3198, \"to\": 3214}, {\"ngram\": \"the nation\", \"from\": 3216, \"to\": 3226}, {\"ngram\": \"autopilot\", \"from\": 3244, \"to\": 3253}, {\"ngram\": \"a caretaker government\", \"from\": 3259, \"to\": 3281}, {\"ngram\": \"routine matters\", \"from\": 3295, \"to\": 3310}, {\"ngram\": \"unspecified lapse\", \"from\": 3315, \"to\": 3332}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 3336, \"to\": 3340}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nevertheless, the post-Olympics blues is certain to creep up sooner than President Emmanuel Macron hopes.\", \"from\": 3343, \"to\": 3448, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3426, \"end\": 3441, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the post-Olympics blues\", \"from\": 3357, \"to\": 3380}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is almost certainly sure that fortune and his own poor judgement in calling for early elections have dealt him a bad hand in the middle of his second and final term as president.\", \"from\": 3449, \"to\": 3630, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fortune\", \"from\": 3482, \"to\": 3489}, {\"ngram\": \"his own poor judgement\", \"from\": 3494, \"to\": 3516}, {\"ngram\": \"early elections\", \"from\": 3532, \"to\": 3547}, {\"ngram\": \"a bad hand\", \"from\": 3563, \"to\": 3573}, {\"ngram\": \"the middle\", \"from\": 3577, \"to\": 3587}, {\"ngram\": \"his second and final term\", \"from\": 3591, \"to\": 3616}, {\"ngram\": \"president\", \"from\": 3620, \"to\": 3629}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bad hand comes at a time that Macron saw himself as paramount leader in the European Union if not, with the US facing an uncertain election, Western democracies as a whole.\", \"from\": 3631, \"to\": 3807, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3665, \"end\": 3671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.258899208786371e-27, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 3720, \"end\": 3725, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999995984581, \"rank\": 3.9367766139289827e-10, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3743, \"end\": 3745, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999627709057527, \"rank\": 3.5693114114658734e-05, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The bad hand\", \"from\": 3631, \"to\": 3643}, {\"ngram\": \"a time\", \"from\": 3653, \"to\": 3659}, {\"ngram\": \"paramount leader\", \"from\": 3687, \"to\": 3703}, {\"ngram\": \"an uncertain election\", \"from\": 3753, \"to\": 3774}, {\"ngram\": \"a whole\", \"from\": 3799, \"to\": 3806}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Or the past two years Macron has assumed a high profile on a number of big issues including the war in Ukraine, the Chinese conundrum, the Middle Eastern powder keg, the terrorist threat and wayward nationalism fed by fear of mass immigration.\", \"from\": 3809, \"to\": 4052, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3831, \"end\": 3837, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.258899208786371e-27, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 3912, \"end\": 3919, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999883350540644, \"rank\": 1.1661189296062899e-05, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 3925, \"end\": 3932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"score\": 0.9977295433432533, \"rank\": 0.002237596721484954, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3948, \"end\": 3962, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Middle_East\", \"score\": 0.9999999547007984, \"rank\": 4.52989539500435e-08, \"text\": \"Middle Eastern\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Middle_East\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Middle_East\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [